external_knowledge:
- Fantasy points are a measure of a player's performance in fantasy sports, combining their real-world statistics (e.g., passing yards, touchdowns) into a numerical value; 
- The change in fantasy points can indicate improvement or decline in a player's performance over time; 
- Injury status and transactions (e.g., trades, drops) can significantly impact a player's fantasy value.

sql:
SELECT player_id, total_fantasy_points, fantasy_points_per_game
FROM fantasy_points
ORDER BY total_fantasy_points DESC;

SELECT passing_yards
FROM passing_stats
WHERE player_id = 1;

SELECT player_id, SUM(rushing_yards) AS total_rushing_yards
FROM rushing_stats
GROUP BY player_id;
